00:27:15.609 --> 00:27:20.690
magnetic fields,
which is currents and charges.

00:27:20.690 --> 00:27:30.568
Okay, so now we are going to
do--let me ask you something.

00:27:30.568 --> 00:27:33.490
When do we keep on modifying
the equations?

00:27:33.490 --> 00:27:35.309
I think I explained that to you.
 

00:27:35.309 --> 00:27:38.519
Why don't we stop now?
 

00:27:38.519 --> 00:27:42.509
Any idea why I'm going to
modify the stuff?

00:27:42.509 --> 00:27:44.788
Do you know?
 

00:27:44.788 --> 00:27:49.890
Do you know when we modify
equations?

00:27:49.890 --> 00:27:51.579
What could be wrong with this
equation?

00:27:51.579 --> 00:27:55.460
Who can convince me it's wrong?
 

00:27:55.460 --> 00:27:59.970
Any idea?
 

00:27:59.970 --> 00:28:03.101
I'm not talking about a
particular thing,

00:28:03.101 --> 00:28:07.563
but I'm talking in general,
what makes people modify their

00:28:07.563 --> 00:28:08.660
equations.
 

00:28:08.660 --> 00:28:09.440
Pardon me?
 

00:28:09.440 --> 00:28:10.420
Student:  New experiment.
 

00:28:10.420 --> 00:28:11.390
Prof: New experiment.
 

00:28:11.390 --> 00:28:15.170
That's the only reason you
modify your results.

00:28:15.170 --> 00:28:17.807
If these things worked,
and it could have been a very

00:28:17.807 --> 00:28:20.801
consistent world in which it
worked, but it is not the whole

00:28:20.801 --> 00:28:21.308
story.
 

00:28:21.308 --> 00:28:24.083
At least one reason it's not
the whole story is,

00:28:24.083 --> 00:28:26.618
rho and J are not always
constant.

00:28:26.618 --> 00:28:29.803
You can have charges shaking
around and you can have

00:28:29.803 --> 00:28:30.490
currents.
 

00:28:30.490 --> 00:28:33.480
You turn them on and off as you
wish.

00:28:33.480 --> 00:28:37.259
One thing is to hope that this
continues to describe them even

00:28:37.259 --> 00:28:38.500
in this situation.
 

00:28:38.500 --> 00:28:41.178
The fact that we derive them
from steady currents and

00:28:41.178 --> 00:28:44.473
densities doesn't mean it has to
fail when they are changing with

00:28:44.473 --> 00:28:47.438
time,
but there is no guarantee that

00:28:47.438 --> 00:28:48.990
they won't change.
 

00:28:48.990 --> 00:28:53.997
So I'm going to now lead you
through the experiments that

00:28:53.997 --> 00:28:58.108
forced us to change some of
these equations.

00:28:58.108 --> 00:29:01.535
So these are called Maxwell's
equations, but they're not the

00:29:01.535 --> 00:29:04.554
real Maxwell equations,
because they're not valid for

00:29:04.554 --> 00:29:06.180
the time dependent case.
 

00:29:06.180 --> 00:29:10.096
I'm going to start the
phenomenon, then we'll see where

00:29:10.096 --> 00:29:11.618
the trouble begins.
 

00:29:11.618 --> 00:29:21.609
So let's take a problem where I
have a uniform magnetic field

00:29:21.609 --> 00:29:25.440
going into the board.
 

00:29:25.440 --> 00:29:29.172
This goes on forever,
but it doesn't go beyond this

00:29:29.172 --> 00:29:29.769
point.
 

00:29:29.769 --> 00:29:33.288
I've only shown you that much.
 

00:29:33.288 --> 00:29:41.288
Now I'm going to take a loop of
wire like this.

00:29:41.288 --> 00:29:48.250
It's got some width w and maybe
some length l..

00:29:48.250 --> 00:29:51.548
And I put a little light bulb
here.

00:29:51.548 --> 00:29:54.847
Then I drag this to the right
with some speed V. And

00:29:54.847 --> 00:30:02.448
this magnetic field
B going into the

00:30:02.448 --> 00:30:05.759
blackboard.
 

00:30:05.759 --> 00:30:08.009
Now if the loop is not moving,
nothing will happen.

00:30:08.009 --> 00:30:13.308
If the loop is moving,
something does happen.

00:30:13.308 --> 00:30:16.798
Now I'm going to ask you what
happens, because this is

00:30:16.798 --> 00:30:18.509
something you must know.
 

00:30:18.509 --> 00:30:19.750
What happens when I drag the
loop?

00:30:19.750 --> 00:30:20.328
Yes?
 

00:30:20.328 --> 00:30:20.950
Student:  The light bulb
will go on.

00:30:20.950 --> 00:30:21.450
Prof: Good.
 

00:30:21.450 --> 00:30:24.798
The light bulb will go on is
the answer that you've got to

00:30:24.798 --> 00:30:25.210
give.
 

00:30:25.210 --> 00:30:27.220
You may not know by how much
and whatnot.

00:30:27.220 --> 00:30:29.679
But first of all,
why would I draw a light bulb

00:30:29.679 --> 00:30:31.230
if it's not going to go on?
 

00:30:31.230 --> 00:30:32.220
That's how you should reason.
 

00:30:32.220 --> 00:30:34.190
That's how my kids did all
their SATs.

00:30:34.190 --> 00:30:36.368
They asked extraneous questions.
 

00:30:36.368 --> 00:30:39.839
One of them is,
you put the light bulb because

00:30:39.839 --> 00:30:41.460
it's going to glow.
 

00:30:41.460 --> 00:30:43.809
So you can ask yourself,
what's going on?

00:30:43.809 --> 00:30:45.309
Why is the light bulb glowing?
 

00:30:45.309 --> 00:30:47.288
Is it some new physics?
 

00:30:47.288 --> 00:30:50.595
The answer is,
whenever youwant a light bulb

00:30:50.595 --> 00:30:53.670
to glow, you're looking for a
battery.

00:30:53.670 --> 00:30:56.470
There is no battery in the
circuit.

00:30:56.470 --> 00:31:00.078
And yet there is an emf,
because every time a charge

00:31:00.078 --> 00:31:02.910
makes one full turn and comes
around,

00:31:02.910 --> 00:31:06.263
it has delivered some work,
because that's what makes this

00:31:06.263 --> 00:31:07.028
thing glow.
 

00:31:07.028 --> 00:31:09.862
You're constantly pumping
energy into the resistor inside

00:31:09.862 --> 00:31:10.470
your bulb.
 

00:31:10.470 --> 00:31:11.720
And who's providing the energy?
 

00:31:11.720 --> 00:31:16.410
These charges are going round
and round doing some work.

00:31:16.410 --> 00:31:21.400
That means something is pushing
them around this loop.

00:31:21.400 --> 00:31:26.373
We defined the emf to be the
line integral of any force per

00:31:26.373 --> 00:31:30.059
unit charge pushing them around
the loop.

00:31:30.059 --> 00:31:33.390
This is per unit charge.
 

00:31:33.390 --> 00:31:40.450
That's got to be not 0.
 

00:31:40.450 --> 00:31:45.290
So what is that force,
and what is the emf is what I

00:31:45.290 --> 00:31:46.618
want to ask.
 

00:31:46.618 --> 00:31:53.710
Do you know what the force
might be?

00:31:53.710 --> 00:31:55.970
And why does it kick in only
when I move the loop?

00:31:55.970 --> 00:31:56.868
Yes?
 

00:31:56.868 --> 00:31:59.785
Student:  The force is
the magnetic force that we

00:31:59.785 --> 00:32:00.210
wrote.
 

00:32:00.210 --> 00:32:01.630
Prof: The v x
B force.

00:32:01.630 --> 00:32:03.396
That's because there's a
v here,

00:32:03.396 --> 00:32:04.838
B into the blackboard.
 

00:32:04.838 --> 00:32:08.519
v x B looks like
that.

00:32:08.519 --> 00:32:12.069
The force is v x
B and it acts only here.

00:32:12.069 --> 00:32:16.130
Let's understand why.
 

00:32:16.130 --> 00:32:20.282
If you come to this portion,
if you take this v x

00:32:20.282 --> 00:32:22.393
B,
this v is this way,

00:32:22.393 --> 00:32:24.772
and B is into the board,
v x B is

00:32:24.772 --> 00:32:25.818
perpendicular to the wire.
 

00:32:25.818 --> 00:32:29.347
But charges cannot go--even if
there's a force perpendicular to

00:32:29.347 --> 00:32:32.707
the wire, it doesn't contribute
to the emf, which I found by

00:32:32.707 --> 00:32:34.130
going along the loop.
 

00:32:34.130 --> 00:32:36.190
So dr is along the loop.
 

00:32:36.190 --> 00:32:39.151
The only way to get that to
contribute is to have a force

00:32:39.151 --> 00:32:40.048
along the loop.
 

00:32:40.048 --> 00:32:43.368
That's only here and it's not
here.

00:32:43.368 --> 00:32:47.348
So the whole force is non-zero
only in that segment.

00:32:47.348 --> 00:32:52.970
So its line integral is equal
to simply the force,

00:32:52.970 --> 00:32:57.099
which is Bv times
w.

00:32:57.099 --> 00:33:00.920
That's the emf.
 

00:33:00.920 --> 00:33:05.247
Any time a charge goes around
the loop once,

00:33:05.247 --> 00:33:08.869
that amount of work is being
done.

00:33:08.869 --> 00:33:10.578
Okay, so that explains it.
 

00:33:10.578 --> 00:33:11.970
We're not in any kind of
trouble.

00:33:11.970 --> 00:33:15.346
In fact, we understand this
problem completely without

00:33:15.346 --> 00:33:17.130
bringing in any new stuff.
 

00:33:17.130 --> 00:33:19.890
But there's one paradox.
 

00:33:19.890 --> 00:33:23.559
We were told the magnetic field
doesn't do any work.

00:33:23.559 --> 00:33:25.278
You remember that?
 

00:33:25.278 --> 00:33:30.316
And yet here is a magnetic
field pushing these charges and

00:33:30.316 --> 00:33:32.259
getting things done.
 

00:33:32.259 --> 00:33:35.368
So what can be going on there?
 

00:33:35.368 --> 00:33:41.279
Student:  It takes work
to move the whole loop.

00:33:41.279 --> 00:33:42.538
Prof: It takes work to
move the loop.

00:33:42.538 --> 00:33:45.580
That is certainly true,
but how about the fact that the

00:33:45.580 --> 00:33:47.890
magnetic field manages to do
some work?

00:33:47.890 --> 00:33:54.558
Is that a problem for you or
not?

00:33:54.558 --> 00:33:57.701
Remember, the original argument
for why it doesn't do any work

00:33:57.701 --> 00:34:00.854
is, the force is
v x B and the

00:34:00.854 --> 00:34:04.718
power is the velocity times the
force and it's 0,

00:34:04.718 --> 00:34:09.550
because v x B is
perpendicular to v.

00:34:09.550 --> 00:34:12.101
But here, v x B
is this way, and the charge is

00:34:12.101 --> 00:34:12.880
moving this way.
 

00:34:12.880 --> 00:34:19.670
It looks like we got some work
done.

00:34:19.670 --> 00:34:24.481
Okay, so the answer is that
this is not the full--there are

00:34:24.481 --> 00:34:26.639
two kinds of velocities.
 

00:34:26.639 --> 00:34:31.059
If you have a current in the
wire, the charges are also

00:34:31.059 --> 00:34:34.659
moving in the wire at some speed
u.

00:34:34.659 --> 00:34:38.268
So the real velocity has got
the velocity because the whole

00:34:38.268 --> 00:34:40.510
loop is moving,
v, and the fact the

00:34:40.510 --> 00:34:43.251
current is moving this way,
u, and w,

00:34:43.251 --> 00:34:47.268
if you like,
is the true velocity.

00:34:47.268 --> 00:34:49.840
And v x B is
actually in that direction.

00:34:49.840 --> 00:34:52.119
That is v x B,
perpendicular to w.

00:34:52.119 --> 00:34:54.010
So let me draw the picture for
you.

00:34:54.010 --> 00:35:03.429
w and w x
B.

00:35:03.429 --> 00:35:04.659
w is made up of two
parts.

00:35:04.659 --> 00:35:12.039
It's got a part v here,
it's got a part u here.

00:35:12.039 --> 00:35:13.989
So the magnetic force is not
just along the wire.

00:35:13.989 --> 00:35:17.550
It's really at this strange
angle.

00:35:17.550 --> 00:35:21.750
And we can easily find out how
much of the force is this part

00:35:21.750 --> 00:35:24.619
and how much of the force is
this part.

00:35:24.619 --> 00:35:33.170
The force here will be--let me
see.

00:35:33.170 --> 00:35:37.733
It will depend on the other
component, so it will depend

00:35:37.733 --> 00:35:42.461
on--yes, the force here is
B times v and the

00:35:42.461 --> 00:35:45.199
power is that times u.
 

00:35:45.199 --> 00:35:49.599
The power is Bvu,
due to this portion.

00:35:49.599 --> 00:35:52.873
But in this side,
if you ask what's the power

00:35:52.873 --> 00:35:57.112
delivered by that component,
it is B times u

00:35:57.112 --> 00:35:59.940
times v,
but with a - sign.

00:35:59.940 --> 00:36:03.657
In other words,
if you resolve this w x

00:36:03.657 --> 00:36:08.456
B into two parts,
the vertical force is due to

00:36:08.456 --> 00:36:12.583
the horizontal velocity,
and the power is that times the

00:36:12.583 --> 00:36:14.159
vertical velocity u.
 

00:36:14.159 --> 00:36:16.460
The horizontal force is due to
the vertical velocity.

00:36:16.460 --> 00:36:18.159
That's how the cross product
works.

00:36:18.159 --> 00:36:20.023
So when you're done,
both are equal to B

00:36:20.023 --> 00:36:21.320
times u times v.
 

00:36:21.320 --> 00:36:23.768
But this is and this is -.
 

00:36:23.768 --> 00:36:26.244
In other words,
in the end, it would like to

00:36:26.244 --> 00:36:29.121
move the charge this way,
because that's the force,

00:36:29.121 --> 00:36:32.230
but it manages to move it along
the wire this way.

00:36:32.230 --> 00:36:36.840
It would like to move it this
way, but it's force to go

00:36:36.840 --> 00:36:37.949
oppositely.
 

00:36:37.949 --> 00:36:41.612
So a force trying to move this
way, this part it is doing work,

00:36:41.612 --> 00:36:43.800
but this part it is not doing
work.

00:36:43.800 --> 00:36:48.041
It has work done on it,
because we forced the electrons

00:36:48.041 --> 00:36:49.849
to move to the right.
 

00:36:49.849 --> 00:36:54.110
Of course, that energy comes
from the person pulling the rod,

00:36:54.110 --> 00:36:57.175
pulling this loop,
because every charge that has

00:36:57.175 --> 00:36:59.501
this force,
it won't just move unless you

00:36:59.501 --> 00:37:01.498
pull it,
and the force you apply is

00:37:01.498 --> 00:37:04.809
really coming from you that
balances the magnetic force.

00:37:04.809 --> 00:37:06.570
So there's yet another force.
 

00:37:06.570 --> 00:37:12.076
That's the force due to me,
and I'm pulling this to balance

00:37:12.076 --> 00:37:14.449
this part of the force.
 

00:37:14.449 --> 00:37:19.679
So what is the role of the
magnetic field?

00:37:19.679 --> 00:37:23.463
It doesn't do any work,
but you need it here,

00:37:23.463 --> 00:37:28.280
because one component of the
magnetic field does work.

00:37:28.280 --> 00:37:31.110
The other component has work
done on it.

00:37:31.110 --> 00:37:34.746
So it takes with one hand and
gives with the other hand,

00:37:34.746 --> 00:37:36.070
but you need that.
 

00:37:36.070 --> 00:37:38.954
It's no used saying,
"I'm not very impressed

00:37:38.954 --> 00:37:41.360
because I did all the hard
work."

00:37:41.360 --> 00:37:45.438
You did all the hard work by
grabbing this loop and pulling

00:37:45.438 --> 00:37:47.213
it,
but I challenge you to go and

00:37:47.213 --> 00:37:50.110
push the individual electrons so
they can move down the wire.

00:37:50.110 --> 00:37:52.730
You cannot even see those
little guys, right?

00:37:52.730 --> 00:37:55.630
But the magnetic field does
that for you.

00:37:55.630 --> 00:37:59.237
So it takes macroscopic
mechanical power,

00:37:59.237 --> 00:38:04.469
turns into microscopic energy
supplied to the electrons.

00:38:04.469 --> 00:38:06.909
Even though the field did not
profit in the end,

00:38:06.909 --> 00:38:09.670
it just delivered to the
electrons what you gave them,

00:38:09.670 --> 00:38:13.552
you need that field to do a
transfer from something you can

00:38:13.552 --> 00:38:16.500
see and pull to something you
cannot see,

00:38:16.500 --> 00:38:17.909
right?
 

00:38:17.909 --> 00:38:19.900
I mean, I give you a light bulb
and you've got all the muscles

00:38:19.900 --> 00:38:20.389
in your hand.
 

00:38:20.389 --> 00:38:22.670
Let's see you make it glow.
 

00:38:22.670 --> 00:38:24.719
You cannot say,
"I have the energy."

00:38:24.719 --> 00:38:26.639
There's no way to transfer it.
 

00:38:26.639 --> 00:38:29.947
That's the role of the magnetic
field, so you shouldn't say it's

00:38:29.947 --> 00:38:30.420
no use.
 

00:38:30.420 --> 00:38:32.710
Anyway, we got that answer.
 

00:38:32.710 --> 00:38:37.811
I'm going to give you another
equivalent way to explain the

00:38:37.811 --> 00:38:39.570
balance of energy.
 

00:38:39.570 --> 00:38:41.440
We all know that the energy is
coming,

00:38:41.440 --> 00:38:44.320
because once the loop carries a
current,

00:38:44.320 --> 00:38:47.010
it's going to be hard for you
to pull the loop,

00:38:47.010 --> 00:38:50.224
so you've got to do some work,
and that will explain the power

00:38:50.224 --> 00:38:50.909
usage here.
 

00:38:50.909 --> 00:38:54.380
So let's calculate the power
two ways.

00:38:54.380 --> 00:39:00.070
The power in the resistor = emf
squared over R.

00:39:00.070 --> 00:39:13.909
emf squared is
B^(2)v^(2)W^(2)/R.

00:39:13.909 --> 00:39:19.010
Now how about the power that I
provide?

00:39:19.010 --> 00:39:20.719
What's the power I provide?
 

00:39:20.719 --> 00:39:23.389
I'm pulling this leg of the
wire here.

00:39:23.389 --> 00:39:25.873
The force on anything,
you remember,

00:39:25.873 --> 00:39:28.711
is BwI,
and I pull it with a force

00:39:28.711 --> 00:39:31.480
v, with a velocity
v.

00:39:31.480 --> 00:39:35.369
That's the power.
 

00:39:35.369 --> 00:39:38.760
So it is Bwv times
I.

00:39:38.760 --> 00:39:41.750
I = emf divided by
R.

00:39:41.750 --> 00:39:48.420
But if you put the emf that we
just got, you will get this.

00:39:48.420 --> 00:39:50.880
So they will match.
 

00:39:50.880 --> 00:39:54.199
So do you understand how this
thing works?

00:39:54.199 --> 00:39:56.010
This is a generator,
if you like.

00:39:56.010 --> 00:39:58.880
If you want to light the bulb
in your house,

00:39:58.880 --> 00:40:01.679
one option is to set up a
magnetic field,

00:40:01.679 --> 00:40:04.719
take the light bulb and connect
it to a rectangle,

00:40:04.719 --> 00:40:06.920
and grab it and keep running.
 

00:40:06.920 --> 00:40:11.768
As long as you're running,
the light bulb will be glowing.

00:40:11.768 --> 00:40:12.929
When do you think it will stop
glowing?

00:40:12.929 --> 00:40:13.659
Yes?
 

00:40:13.659 --> 00:40:16.309
Student:  I'm sorry,
what does that word say?

00:40:16.309 --> 00:40:18.119
Prof: This one?
 

00:40:18.119 --> 00:40:28.989
The power that I provide.
 

00:40:28.989 --> 00:40:32.440
Okay, I'm just balancing the
power loss in the resistor.

00:40:32.440 --> 00:40:33.420
Are you with me now?
 

00:40:33.420 --> 00:40:35.409
You understand the two things?
 

00:40:35.409 --> 00:40:38.550
I take the force I apply on the
wire, multiply by the velocity

00:40:38.550 --> 00:40:39.579
with which I pull.
 

00:40:39.579 --> 00:40:40.639
That's the power.
 

00:40:40.639 --> 00:40:42.219
Likewise I take I^(2)R.
 

00:40:42.219 --> 00:40:44.059
That's the electric power
dissipated.

00:40:44.059 --> 00:40:47.518
And of course, they balance.
 

00:40:47.518 --> 00:40:54.157
Notice that once the loop is
fully inside the magnetic field,

00:40:54.157 --> 00:40:58.030
the light bulb will stop
glowing.

00:40:58.030 --> 00:40:59.400
Do you know why?
 

00:40:59.400 --> 00:41:00.179
Can you see why?
 

00:41:00.179 --> 00:41:00.760
Yes?
 

00:41:00.760 --> 00:41:02.715
Student:  Because the
flux in the loop isn't changing

00:41:02.715 --> 00:41:03.079
any more.
 

00:41:03.079 --> 00:41:03.889
Prof: No, no.
 

00:41:03.889 --> 00:41:07.039
You're pulling new laws,
in terms of what I've told you.

00:41:07.039 --> 00:41:10.713
Student:  The magnetic
field, there's no new field

00:41:10.713 --> 00:41:12.420
coming through the wire.
 

00:41:12.420 --> 00:41:15.630
