00:44:58.440 --> 00:45:01.159
E and B will do.
 

00:45:01.159 --> 00:45:03.530
In which case,
what are we saying?

00:45:03.530 --> 00:45:06.548
We are saying that in the other
frame of reference,

00:45:06.548 --> 00:45:09.447
where the loop is fixed and the
magnet is moving,

00:45:09.447 --> 00:45:11.320
there is an electric field.
 

00:45:11.320 --> 00:45:16.594
Not only that,
it's an electric field whose

00:45:16.594 --> 00:45:21.023
line integral is not 0,
because it is still true that

00:45:21.023 --> 00:45:23.550
charges in the loop are going
round and round and doing work,

00:45:23.550 --> 00:45:25.860
and someone's providing work
for every charge that goes

00:45:25.860 --> 00:45:26.630
around the loop.
 

00:45:26.630 --> 00:45:30.809
And the emf is the work done on
a unit charge.

00:45:30.809 --> 00:45:36.117
So this makes us believe now
that whenever there's a changing

00:45:36.117 --> 00:45:40.099
magnetic field,
there is an electric field.

00:45:40.099 --> 00:45:44.018
This is an electric field of
brand new origin.

00:45:44.018 --> 00:45:49.065
All the electric fields you
studied before were produced by

00:45:49.065 --> 00:45:51.590
charges, by coulombs force.
 

00:45:51.590 --> 00:45:54.349
This says, without the help of
any charge.

00:45:54.349 --> 00:45:55.929
Charges are nowhere to be found.
 

00:45:55.929 --> 00:45:57.500
They could be infinitely far.
 

00:45:57.500 --> 00:46:01.119
If I change the magnetic field,
I'm going to get an electric

00:46:01.119 --> 00:46:01.610
field.
 

00:46:01.610 --> 00:46:04.619
Of course, we have to find out
what is the connection.

00:46:04.619 --> 00:46:06.130
How much electric field do you
get?

00:46:06.130 --> 00:46:08.320
How is it connected to the
magnetic field?

00:46:08.320 --> 00:46:11.452
These are things you have to
deduce and you cannot deduce

00:46:11.452 --> 00:46:12.460
them from logic.
 

00:46:12.460 --> 00:46:15.449
You can deduce them only from
experiment.

00:46:15.449 --> 00:46:16.739
Certain things come from logic.
 

00:46:16.739 --> 00:46:19.099
If you have an equation,
you solve it using mathematics.

00:46:19.099 --> 00:46:20.869
If you like,
that's a kind of logic.

00:46:20.869 --> 00:46:24.358
Or you use symmetry and say,
"If I turn the wire and it

00:46:24.358 --> 00:46:26.782
looks the same,
the answer should look the

00:46:26.782 --> 00:46:28.260
same" and so on.
 

00:46:28.260 --> 00:46:32.492
But what electric field should
be produced by changing magnetic

00:46:32.492 --> 00:46:35.360
field you cannot derive from
pure logic.

00:46:35.360 --> 00:46:38.400
If you combine it with other
principles like relativity,

00:46:38.400 --> 00:46:40.340
you could try to get them,
but right now,

00:46:40.340 --> 00:46:42.932
with what we have,
we just know that in the moving

00:46:42.932 --> 00:46:44.630
frame--
look, you don't need Einstein

00:46:44.630 --> 00:46:45.389
to tell you this.
 

00:46:45.389 --> 00:46:48.894
Even before Einstein,
you knew that you're certainly

00:46:48.894 --> 00:46:52.813
free to imagine a loop being
fixed and somebody moving the

00:46:52.813 --> 00:46:53.570
magnet.
 

00:46:53.570 --> 00:46:57.420
And everything in you tells you
the answer's got to be the same,

00:46:57.420 --> 00:46:59.956
because in the end,
it's the relative motion

00:46:59.956 --> 00:47:02.730
between the loop and the magnet
that decides.

00:47:02.730 --> 00:47:05.005
And if you provide the same
relative motion,

00:47:05.005 --> 00:47:06.909
you've got to get the same
answer.

00:47:06.909 --> 00:47:09.342
And the only way to get that is
to say when there's a changing

00:47:09.342 --> 00:47:10.989
magnetic field,
I have an electric field,

00:47:10.989 --> 00:47:13.606
and furthermore,
electric field which is no

00:47:13.606 --> 00:47:17.800
longer conservative because its
line integral is not 0.

00:47:17.800 --> 00:47:19.699
So we've got to find out what
it is.

00:47:19.699 --> 00:47:23.882
So I'm going to tell you now an
equation that really answers

00:47:23.882 --> 00:47:26.789
that question,
and we cannot derive it.

00:47:26.789 --> 00:47:29.010
It's a summary of a lot of
experiment.

00:47:29.010 --> 00:47:38.920
And that says that the
electromotive force--

00:47:38.920 --> 00:47:42.760
in fact, due to electric and
magnetic origin,

00:47:42.760 --> 00:47:49.829
em = -d
Î¦/dt,

00:47:49.829 --> 00:47:58.699
and I'll tell you what this
equation means.

00:47:58.699 --> 00:48:08.230
So you take a loop,
some contour c,

00:48:08.230 --> 00:48:14.480
and you define Î¦
to be equal to the integral of

00:48:14.480 --> 00:48:22.230
the magnetic field on a surface
whose boundary is this loop.

00:48:22.230 --> 00:48:27.699
That's called the magnetic flux.
 

00:48:27.699 --> 00:48:30.159
So you know operationally how
to calculate it.

00:48:30.159 --> 00:48:32.719
Take any surface you want.
 

00:48:32.719 --> 00:48:35.054
It may be a flat one,
a bulging one,

00:48:35.054 --> 00:48:36.190
doesn't matter.
 

00:48:36.190 --> 00:48:40.228
Take the flux going through any
surface with that as the

00:48:40.228 --> 00:48:44.632
boundary, and find its rate of
change, and that will be equal

00:48:44.632 --> 00:48:46.909
to the electromotive force.
 

00:48:46.909 --> 00:48:52.751
In fact, you just write
E electromotive force,

00:48:52.751 --> 00:48:56.909
= -d
Î¦/dt.

00:48:56.909 --> 00:48:59.643
So you know operationally how
to find this thing,

00:48:59.643 --> 00:49:00.099
right?
 

00:49:00.099 --> 00:49:03.855
Now again, you may ask,
"Which surface do you want

00:49:03.855 --> 00:49:06.150
to take for a given loop?"
 

00:49:06.150 --> 00:49:08.556
This flat one or the curvy one
or the one with more bumps in

00:49:08.556 --> 00:49:08.760
it?
 

00:49:08.760 --> 00:49:11.409
The answer is,
again, it does not matter.

00:49:11.409 --> 00:49:12.420
The reason is the same.
 

00:49:12.420 --> 00:49:16.005
If you've got some magnetic
lines coming through this guy,

00:49:16.005 --> 00:49:19.465
they also have to come out
through that guy because they

00:49:19.465 --> 00:49:20.409
don't stop.
 

00:49:20.409 --> 00:49:23.510
Magnetic field lines that enter
one surface have to also enter

00:49:23.510 --> 00:49:26.610
another one with the same edge,
because they cannot escape.

00:49:26.610 --> 00:49:28.210
So you can take any surface you
like.

00:49:28.210 --> 00:49:31.420
So whenever you have these laws
where a surface is invoked,

00:49:31.420 --> 00:49:34.039
and it's ambiguous and not
defined by the perimeter,

00:49:34.039 --> 00:49:36.692
the answer is,
it doesn't matter which

00:49:36.692 --> 00:49:37.409
surface.
 

00:49:37.409 --> 00:49:40.309
The reason is that field lines
don't stop and end,

00:49:40.309 --> 00:49:43.800
therefore whatever enters this
surface has to leave this.

00:49:43.800 --> 00:49:47.402
If you had magnetic monopoles,
the lines can enter this and

00:49:47.402 --> 00:49:49.639
terminate on a negative
monopole,

00:49:49.639 --> 00:49:55.079
then of course it won't be
true, but you don't have that.

00:49:55.079 --> 00:49:59.706
Now this - sign has got the
name Lenz attached to it,

00:49:59.706 --> 00:50:02.820
and this thing is called
Faraday.

00:50:02.820 --> 00:50:03.789
Faraday and Lenz.
 

00:50:03.789 --> 00:50:08.070
And I will tell you what the -
sign due to Lenz means.

00:50:08.070 --> 00:50:13.505
Lenz's law tells you that if
you change the magnetic flux in

00:50:13.505 --> 00:50:18.389
a system, there's going to be a
very long sentence.

00:50:18.389 --> 00:50:21.670
If you take the magnetic flux
in a system and it changes,

00:50:21.670 --> 00:50:26.420
it will induce an emf which,
if it could drive a current,

00:50:26.420 --> 00:50:31.159
will do so in order to fight
that change.

00:50:31.159 --> 00:50:33.690
That's why it's a long
statement.

00:50:33.690 --> 00:50:36.367
In other words,
if you had a real circuit and

00:50:36.367 --> 00:50:38.925
you shove it into region of
changing field,

00:50:38.925 --> 00:50:41.360
an emf will start driving a
current.

00:50:41.360 --> 00:50:44.440
That current itself will
produce its own magnetic field.

00:50:44.440 --> 00:50:45.550
Which way will it point?
 

00:50:45.550 --> 00:50:48.413
The answer is,
it will point it such a way as

00:50:48.413 --> 00:50:50.170
to neutralize the change.
 

00:50:50.170 --> 00:50:54.449
For example,
if you took a loop and it had

00:50:54.449 --> 00:50:58.818
some flux going through it,
if you tried to increase the

00:50:58.818 --> 00:51:01.500
flux going through it,
it will try to decrease it,

00:51:01.500 --> 00:51:03.659
so the current will flow like
that.

00:51:03.659 --> 00:51:05.954
If you try to decrease the flux
through it, it will try to prop

00:51:05.954 --> 00:51:06.880
it up to its old value.
 

00:51:06.880 --> 00:51:08.050
The current will go like that.
 

00:51:08.050 --> 00:51:11.059
That helps you find the
direction of the current.

00:51:11.059 --> 00:51:15.730
The emf will be such as to
neutralize the change.

00:51:15.730 --> 00:51:18.530
It does not necessarily oppose
the external field,

00:51:18.530 --> 00:51:19.730
the magnetic field.
 

00:51:19.730 --> 00:51:21.710
It opposes the change in the
magnetic field.

00:51:21.710 --> 00:51:23.300
That's what I want you to
understand.

00:51:23.300 --> 00:51:26.603
For example,
suppose I've got lines coming

00:51:26.603 --> 00:51:27.489
out here.
 

00:51:27.489 --> 00:51:31.367
And they get weaker,
namely some source of magnetism

00:51:31.367 --> 00:51:33.268
makes the lines weaker.
 

00:51:33.268 --> 00:51:37.320
Then the current will start
going this way to prop up the

00:51:37.320 --> 00:51:39.489
thing back to its old value.
 

00:51:39.489 --> 00:51:41.590
That's what you have to
understand.

00:51:41.590 --> 00:51:44.735
That's the meaning of the -
sign and that's going to guide

00:51:44.735 --> 00:51:47.219
us much better than all the
cross products.

00:51:47.219 --> 00:51:50.697
Now I will show you that with
this one law,

00:51:50.697 --> 00:51:53.099
